Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve and peel the
@red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop the potato and onion onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle},
season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, sprinkle over the
@dried oregano{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, pop half the @garlic cloves{4} (unpeeled) into a small piece of
#foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel until
soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut it into 3 slices per person.
Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{}.

Once hot, add the grated garlic and @smoked paprika{1%sachet}. Fry for
~{1%minute}.

Stir through the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).
Bring up to the boil, then lower to a simmer and cook until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a plate lined
with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Once the halloumi is cooked, remove from the heat and drizzle over the
@red pepper chilli jelly{25%g}. Turn the halloumi in the glaze until well
coated.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of
the skin and mash with a #fork{}. Mix together in a small bowl with the
@mayonnaise{96%g} and season with salt and pepper. Set your aioli aside.

Share your roasted veg between your #serving bowls{} and pour the bravas sauce
all over.

Drizzle over your garlic aioli.

Arrange your glazed halloumi on top and serve with a handful of
@wild rocket{20%g} to finish.

Enjoy!